## 1. Phase 1 - Database Detection

**Do not skip to questions.** Detect database usage first.

### 1.1 Agent Actions (Silent)

```
SEARCH for database indicators:
  - Schema files (*.sql, schema.prisma, alembic/versions/*, db/migrate/*, migrations/*)
  - Database configuration (database.yml, ormconfig.json, knexfile.js, .env.example)
  - ORM imports (SQLAlchemy, Prisma, TypeORM, Django ORM, Sequelize, Knex, mongoose)
  - Database client libraries (psycopg2, pymongo, redis-py, pg, mysql2, mongodb)
  - Connection code (database.ts, db.py, connection.js, config/database.*)
  - Data access code (repositories/, dao/, queries/, models/)
  - GCP imports (@google-cloud/spanner, @google-cloud/firestore, @google-cloud/bigquery, @google-cloud/datastore)
  - Azure imports (@azure/cosmos, @azure/data-tables, azure-storage, mssql with azure)

IDENTIFY database systems:
  - PostgreSQL (pg, psycopg2, postgresql://)
  - MySQL (mysql2, pymysql, mysql://)
  - MongoDB (mongoose, pymongo, mongodb://)
  - Redis (redis, ioredis, redis://)
  - SQLite (sqlite3, better-sqlite3)
  - GCP services (Cloud SQL, Cloud Spanner, Firestore, BigQuery, Bigtable, Memorystore)
  - Azure services (Azure SQL, Azure Database for PostgreSQL/MySQL, Cosmos DB, Azure Cache)
  - Other (Cassandra, DynamoDB, Elasticsearch, Neo4j)

ANALYSE schemas:
  - Find main schema file
  - Count tables/collections
  - Identify naming conventions (snake_case, camelCase)
  - Note primary key patterns (UUIDs, serial, composite)

FIND data access code:
  - Repository/DAO directories
  - ORM usage locations
  - Query file locations

IDENTIFY migration tool:
  - Tool name (Alembic, TypeORM, Prisma, Flyway, Django)
  - Migration directory location
```

